summary:
Can you imagine Steve and Tony talking and figuring everything out right after the war is won? 
Can you imagine everyone...
body:
Can you imagine Steve and Tony talking and figuring everything out right after the war is won?

Can you imagine everyone celebrating in victory, all together?

Picture the: Clint sat on the couch and Nat with her head on his lap. Thor standing still next to the guardians, literally all of them and Groot sleeping on his shoulder and Loki standing by his side. Steve and Tony talking on the chairs in the kitchen while Wanda and Vision are talking by the other side of the table. Professor Hulk is discussing of some sort of scienze-stuff with Ant-man, who’s sitting on an armchair while Hope and Cassie are making fun of him. Bucky and Sam are talking of some dumb shit as usual. Pepper is in Morgan’s bedroom and she’s telling her a story. T’Challa is happy in Wakanda with his whole family. Everyone is happy. Everyone is alive.

Imagine how happy everyone could have been.

summary: Hey! I loved your sleepless night fic and was wondering if you could do one similar where the reader is part of the winter...
question: Hey! I loved your sleepless night fic and was wondering if you could do one similar where the reader is part of the winter soldier cast, but still pretty young(like def the baby of the group like Tom) and really close to Chris, Seb, Anthony and they’re walking the premiere carpet and someone grabs the reader like paparazzi or a crazy fan and he won’t let go and they all go like big brother protective over the reader
answer:
Come On, Little Lady, Give Us A Smile (Avengers Cast x Teen!Reader)

Avengers Cast Masterlist

A/N: Glad you enjoyed the Sleepless Night fic!! Hope you enjoy this one! 

Cast Members: Sebastian Stan, Chris Evans, and Anthony Mackie

Warnings: Creepers. a dude being a huge creep

Word Count: 635



Y/A = Your Age

The sounds of the crowd made you feel pumped for the night’s event. You had gotten a role as a young mutant for the movie Captain America: The Winter Soldier, a role that had changed your career for the better. You were currently at the premiere, you were wearing a backless, silky long grey dress, the color to match your characters tactical suit. You looked around the carpet looking for your costars, unfortunately, you weren’t able to do the press tour with them, due to the fact that you were busy in New Zealand filming a Star Wars movie so it’s been a long time since you’ve seen your costars. While filming the movie, you’ve grown close to Evans, Stan, and Mackie. To you they were older brothers, they way they always teased you and yet were so protective of you.

Your manager led you to one of the interviewers, you quickly struck up a conversation with them.

“I hear you’re filming a Star Wars movie that has yet to be named, can you tell us anything about that?”

You chuckled, “Sorry, I swore secrecy when I signed the contract,” you made a motion with your fingers as if you were zipping your lips.

The interviewer laughed, “It’s still huge though! First Marvel and now Star wars at only (Y/A) just wow! And by the way, you look gorgeous tonight! This dress, it might stir up some drama later within the fashion blogs but damn girl!”

“Yeah, it’s definitely might get some buzz, but I don’t care, I think I look amazing for once so I’m gonna own this look!”

“You go, girl!” She said, “well, thank you for talking with us!” You thanked the interview and walked over to the fans that were calling your name. You signed some posters and even took photos with some of them.

One of the fans kept looking over to the paparazzi that was taking photos of you, you could tell that she was uncomfortable, you looked over to the paparazzi asking him politely to stop taking photos because it was making the fans a bit uncomfortable. He walked over to you, placing an arm around your waist, “oh come on, baby, you know the real view of the photo is going to be you. So, why don’t you give me a smile?” Your eyes widen at the comment, you attempted to take off his arm off your waist.

“Hey!” You heard a familiar voice say, you turned around to see the brotherly trio walking over to you, “don’t touch her like that,” Sebastian warned.

The paparazzi quickly let go of you, “sorry, my man, couldn’t help myself, you know how it is sometimes.”

“No, I don’t,” Sebastian said with disgust.

“Look just do us all a favor and get your creepy self out of here,” Anthony said as he walked up to the paparazzi. The paparazzi gave Anthony a nod and walked off.

“You alright?” Chris asked as he walked over to you, giving you a hug.

“Yeah, just a bit startled,” you said as you hugged Chris back. It took a few minutes to calm down from the incident, once you did, it was back to normal.

“Missed you, kid!” Anthony exclaimed as he hugged you, “thought you were gonna forget about your Marvel family since you started working for the Star Wars franchise.”

“Yeah, we were starting to think you were getting too good for us!” Sebastian teased.

You rolled your eyes, “You guys will always be above, Star Wars, you know that” you gave Sebastian a hug. “Thanks for coming to my rescue.”

“We gotta protect the baby of the group, right fellas?” You rolled your eyes at Anthony’s comment, you may hate some of the attention fame brought but you didn’t regret meeting these three men in front of you.

It can be difficult but not impossible.
